🧠 1. SIGNAL SCORE SYSTEM (REAL IMPLEMENTATION)

This is your internal “quality of signal” metric.

🔹 Core idea

Not all swipes are equal.

You weight users based on how useful their decisions are.

⸻

📊 Components

A. Consistency Score

How stable are their preferences?

if user reverses same pair often:
    consistency -= penalty
else:
    consistency += reward

Signal:
	•	High = strong identity
	•	Low = noisy / exploratory

⸻

B. Discrimination Score

Do they meaningfully differentiate?

if user picks same type blindly:
    discrimination -= penalty
else if choices vary with context:
    discrimination += reward

Signal:
	•	High = nuanced taste
	•	Low = random / lazy

⸻

C. Confidence Score

Derived from:
	•	hesitation time
	•	“on deck” usage
	•	re-evaluations

if user uses "on deck" intelligently:
    confidence += reward

if rapid random swiping:
    confidence -= penalty


⸻

D. Coverage Score

How much of the space they’ve explored

coverage = unique_entities_seen / total_entities


⸻

E. Engagement Depth

Did they:
	•	open profiles?
	•	view art variants?
	•	compare closely?

⸻

🧮 Final Signal Score

signal_score =
    0.30 * consistency +
    0.25 * discrimination +
    0.20 * confidence +
    0.15 * coverage +
    0.10 * depth


⸻

🧠 IMPORTANT

This is:
	•	internal weighting
	•	not a social leaderboard

You don’t want:
❌ “high IQ taste users”

You want:
✅ better model accuracy

